The paper deals with the multiway cut problem, which is a classic problem in theoretical computer science and optimization. The techniques used in the paper involve geometric tools and combinatorial analysis, which are common in areas such as computational geometry (cs.CG), combinatorics (cs.DM), and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the analysis of approximation algorithms, which is a topic in the subfield of approximation algorithms (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS).
